Mafdet's harbor district pit fighting circuit predates the Kowloon circuit and operates under Maritime Law provisions giving operators different regulatory status.
The Strandline Compact's trade network creates sustained demand for physical security services; Brawler practitioners find consistent employment in cargo security and dispute resolution.
Harbor Wardens' Ledger Houses classify Brawler security practitioners under labor contract registry provisions.
The swift-court's jurisdiction over oath-breaking extends to fighting pit agreements — a fighter violating agreed match terms faces swift-court proceedings, which Mafdet's pit operators treat as a quality assurance mechanism the Kowloon circuit lacks.

