Ashborn forge-culture aligns naturally with the Brawler tradition's core epistemology: knowledge tested against resistance is reliable; untested knowledge is speculation. The pit's adversarial testing is the physical analogue of forge-testing.
Ashborn practitioners who enter the Brawler tradition advance quickly through early stages because demonstration-based instruction matches Ashborn learning culture, which similarly privileges hands-on experience over theoretical frameworks.
Ashborn Brawlers in Kowloon's harbor district are disproportionately represented in the enforcement corps relative to their population, reflecting both aptitude and cultural fit with the corps' direct-action orientation.

